5 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Direction to department of public health and human services. (1)
6 The legislature directs the department of public health and human services to apply TO THE CENTERS FOR
7 MEDICARE AND MEDICAID SERVICES for a ANY NECESSARY WAIVER AND state plan amendment no later than January
8 1, 2028 2026, to make assisted living facility services currently covered under the big sky waiver a service
9 covered under the community first choice option available under the medicaid program TO ALLOW FOR MEDICAID-
10 COVERED ASSISTED LIVING SERVICES TO BE REMOVED FROM THE BIG SKY WAIVER PROGRAM AND TO BE COVERED BY
11 THE COMMUNITY FIRST CHOICE OPTION PROGRAM.
12 (2) IT IS THE INTENT OF THE LEGISLATURE THAT THE DEPARTMENT TRANSFER FUNDING FOR ASSISTED
13 LIVING SERVICES FROM THE BIG SKY WAIVER PROGRAM TO THE COMMUNITY FIRST CHOICE OPTION PROGRAM AS
14 INDIVIDUALS ARE MOVED FROM THE BIG SKY WAIVER PROGRAM, AND ITS WAITLIST, TO THE COMMUNITY FIRST CHOICE
15 OPTION PROGRAM. THE AMOUNT TRANSFERRED WILL BE THE ACTUAL COST OF SERVING THE INDIVIDUALS RECEIVING
16 ASSISTED LIVING SERVICES UNDER THE COMMUNITY FIRST CHOICE OPTION PROGRAM.
17 (3) SAVINGS GENERATED FROM THE TRANSFER OF INDIVIDUALS TO A LOWER-COST OPTION WILL REMAIN IN
18 THE BIG SKY WAIVER PROGRAM TO BE USED TO SERVE INDIVIDUALS WAITING FOR HOME AND COMMUNITY-BASED
19 SERVICES REMAINING IN THE WAIVER are transferred into the general fund.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Reporting requirements -- big sky waiver and community first
22 choice programs. (1) Each quarter of the 2029 2027 biennium, the department of public health and human
23 services shall report the following information for the preceding quarter to the health and human services
